attackingDamage:
{# Attacking}
Thar be multiple methods o' attack:
- Ye will "Auto Attack" {*untamed creatures*} with a melee attack when ye walk into them. 
- Ye can melee attack {*any creature or person*} with th' "Attack" action, available in th' {(HELP/ACTIONS):actions menu}, with {BINDINGS:GameActions}, then {BINDINGS:GameActionAttack}.
- Ye can throw items or fire ranged projectiles with th' "Throw" and "Fire" actions.

Ye can disable th' "Auto Attack" feature in th' {(DIALOG/3):Gameplay Settings dialog}, opened with {BINDINGS:DialogOptions}. While th' feature be disabled, walkin' into some smaller creatures allows ye t' swap positions with them.

{# Damage Types}
Damage dealt by weapons and creatures has one or more "damage types". Thar be five possible damage types: {!DAMAGE_TYPE 4}, {!DAMAGE_TYPE 2}, {!DAMAGE_TYPE 1}, {!DAMAGE_TYPE 8}, and {!DAMAGE_TYPE 16}.

Equipment and creatures may be {*vulnerable*}, {*resistant*}, or entirely {*immune*} t' certain damage types.

Fer more information, see th' {*Attack Effectiveness*} section below.

{## Tooltips}
- Weapon tooltips will reveal th' damage types they deal and equipment tooltips will reveal th' damage types they be vulnerable or resistant to.
- Creature tooltips will reveal yer current understandin' o' its vulnerabilities and resistances. This be based on which resistances & vulnerabilities you've discovered through attackin' th' creature with various damage types, and yer skill in {$SKILL:2}.

{# Attack Effectiveness}
If a weapon has multiple damage types, it will consider yer attack t' be usin' all o' them. Th' damage dealt be calculated with th' formula {*attack \- defense + vulnerabilities \- resistances*}.

{## Example:}
- Ye hit a scorpion with a wooden sword that deals {*3 blunt & piercin' damage*}.
- Scorpions have a {*resistance o' 1 against piercin'*} and a {*vulnerability o' 2 from blunt*}, with a {*base defense o' 2*}.

Th' scorpion would take:
- {#--COLOR-STAT-ATTACK:3 base damage}
- {#--COLOR-STAT-DEFENSE:-2 damage fer its defense}
- {#--COLOR-VULNERABILITY:+2 damage fer its blunt vulnerability}
- {#--COLOR-STAT-DEFENSE:-1 damage fer its piercin' resist}
Resultin' in a total o' {*2 damage*}.

{.SECONDARY:Note that other factors like yer skills be not considered in this example.}

Ye can review yer current vulnerabilities and resistances in th' {$STAT:6} tooltip, viewable by movin' th' mouse over th' stat with th' shield icon.

{# Tactics}
Yer accuracy and base damage dealt in all combat be based on {$SKILL:21}.

T' get an overview o' th' damage yer dealin' and what contributes t' it, see th' {$STAT:5} tooltip, viewable by movin' th' mouse over th' stat with th' sword icon.

{# Dual Wielding}
Most weapons can only be used on their own. Equippin' two swords, fer example, will only attack with one o' them, and th' other slot will be used purely fer defense.

Some weapons, however, have th' {*{!ITEM_GROUP -9885}*} groupin'. When ye have two dual-wieldable weapons equipped:
- Yer attack will use {*all*} damage types on {*both*} weapons.
- Ye will deal damage equivalent t' yer main hand weapon, plus some damage from yer off-handed weapon based on yer {$SKILL:32} skill.
- Ye will use more {$STAT:1} than when only attackin' with one weapon.
- Both weapons will take durability damage.

{# Parrying}
Havin' an item equipped in {*both yer main hand and off hand*} allows ye t' parry attacks. This {*increases yer base defense*}, and upon successfully parryin' an attack, {*mitigates some incomin' damage*}.

Th' increased defense and damage mitigation chance from parryin' be dependent on yer {$SKILL:18} skill.

Ye can review yer defensive stats in th' {$STAT:6} tooltip, viewable by movin' th' mouse over th' stat with th' shield icon.

restingSleeping:
Restin' and sleepin' be different actions and have their own set o' pros and cons.

{_Restin'_}
1. Ye be able t' cancel out o' restin'.
2. Reduces hunger and thirst rate, but not as much as sleepin'.
3. Increases stamina and health regeneration, but not as much as sleepin'.
4. Ye cannot rest while yer stamina be full. Rest will automatically be cancelled once yer stamina be full.
5. Fire sources have no impact on regeneration or rest length.

{_Sleepin'_}
1. Ye cannot cancel out o' sleepin', potentially leadin' t' oversleepin' or other dangers.
2. Reduces hunger and thirst rate more so than restin'.
3. Increases stamina and health regeneration more so than restin'.
4. Ye can sleep indefinitely regardless o' stamina value.
5. Fire sources (lit campfires, lit furnaces, coolin' lava, etc.) will produce better stamina and health regeneration as well as increase th' amount o' turns ye can sleep in one {(HELP/ACTIONS):action}.

{_Items & Doodads_}
By usin' a beddin' item or {(HELP/DOODADS):doodad} (like a placed bedroll) ye will receive better stamina and health regeneration. Restin' or sleepin' on th' ground will produce th' worst regenerative effects. A message will appear warnin' ye o' this effect.

{_Creatures_}
Ye will not be able t' rest or sleep effectively while untamed creatures be nearby. If they be breakin' doodads (like doors and walls) within a radius o' up t' 5 tiles away, ye may wake up. If they be up t' 3 tiles away, ye may also wake up from hearin' them stirrin'.

{_Terrain_}
Restin' or sleepin' on certain terrain will decrease th' maximum amount o' turns ye can rest or sleep in one action. This includes terrain like water, snow, etc. A message will appear warnin' ye o' this effect.

{_Campin'_}
Th' higher yer {$SKILL:6} skill, th' higher th' maximum amount o' turns ye can rest or sleep in one action.

{_Darkness_}
Darkness in th' form o' nighttime or caves will increase th' amount o' turns ye can rest or sleep in one action.

{_Multiplayer & Real-time_}
Restin' and sleepin' work differently when playin' a multiplayer game or settin' th' mode t' "real-time" turns, in that performin' th' rest/sleep actions will no longer progress time (or pass turns). Its use be shifted towards a regenerative role exclusively in these modes.

gameModes:
{# Game Modes}

{_Hardcore_}

{#--TEXT-SECONDARY:Difficulty:} Medium t' High

Th' default and definitive way t' play.
- Death be permanent; however, ye can respawn which will reset th' game t' "Casual" mode.


{_Casual_}

{#--TEXT-SECONDARY:Difficulty:} Low

- Dyin' will respawn ye in th' last place ye rested or slept, with yer items dropped at th' location o' yer demise.
- Most creatures be neutral/peaceful unless attacked.
- {(HELP/CreatureTerritories):Creature territories} will still impact creature spawn types and frequency, but ye can engage with them at yer choosin'.
- {(HELP/MILESTONES):Milestones} be disabled in this mode.


{_Challenge_}

{#--TEXT-SECONDARY:Difficulty:} High

- Randomized difficulty modifiers and a unique set o' quests, intended fer quick play sessions.
- Savin' be disabled in this mode.
- Choose th' "Daily" option t' compete with others or yerself fer highscores.
- Due t' th' modifiers and set o' quests that must be performed, difficulty in this mode will always be high regardless o' {(HELP/CreatureTerritories):creature territories}.
- Score be gained by raisin' stats and skills as per normal, but also when completin' quests. Score decays as turns pass, so it's best t' complete quests and th' challenge as smartly as possible.
- Only "Challenge Mode" {(HELP/MILESTONES):milestones} be obtainable in this mode.


{_Custom_}

- Allows ye t' customize yer game t' yer likin', choosin' from a large set o' difficulty modifiers.
- Some o' th' customizable aspects be features o' th' above modes (peaceful creatures, respawnin', etc.).
- {(HELP/MILESTONES):Milestones} be disabled in this mode.


{#--TEXT-SECONDARY:{/Whether in Challenge Mode or Custom Mode, ye can see which modifiers be enabled with th' pause menu by usin' {BINDINGS:GamePause}/}}


{# Turn Modes}
Dependin' on if ye be playin' a single player or multiplayer game, ye can choose from th' followin' turn modes:


{_Manual Turns_}

{#--TEXT-SECONDARY:Difficulty:} Low

Turns only pass as players perform actions (also known as "turn-based"). This mode be only available in single player mode.


{_Simulated Turns_}

{#--TEXT-SECONDARY:Difficulty:} Medium

Turns happen automatically as lon' as player(s) be performin' actions. This mode be only available in multiplayer mode.


{_Real-time Turns_}

{#--TEXT-SECONDARY:Difficulty:} High

Turns happen automatically as time passes. Ye can modify th' time between turns with th' "Tick Time" settin'.


